parameter.name: Emax for GLP-1 agonist on fat loss (rate of fat change)

body.p: Adjusted to match clinical weight loss rates:

ul.li: Typical weight loss: 2-4 kg over 26 weeks
Emax accounts for maximum effect at saturating drug concentrations

parameter.name: gamma for GLP-1 agonist on fat loss
EC50 for GLP-1 agonist on fat loss

body.p: Adjusted to physiologically relevant range:

ul.li: Typical dulaglutide Cmax: 10-100 ng/mL after 0.75-1.5 mg dose
Converted to molar: ~3-30 µM (3e-6 to 3e-5 mM)
EC50 set to mid-range for reasonable dose-response

parameter.name: rate normalization FPG with GLP-1 agonist

body.p: set based on turnover of erythrocytes
halflife turnover of erythrocytes of tau = 4 month k = ln(2) / (4 * 30 * 24 * 60) [1/min]
set so that the HbA1c is 5% at steady state for 5 mM FPG
1.0: normal function; <1.0: reduced function as reduced cardiac output;
